    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - IC BUS - FENDER MOUNTED
        MIRRORS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FENDER MOUNTED MIRRORS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>MIRROR REMOVAL</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check state and local regulations on mirror type and mounting that may be required.</para>
                </note>
                <important>
                    <para>DO NOT ALTER OR REPLACE MIRROR TYPE WITHOUT PERMISSION OF THE MIRROR MANUFACTURER.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900527">Figure 27</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900528">Figure 28</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900527" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900527.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Fender Mounted Rear View Mirror, Passenger Side Shown</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CURVED MOUNTING BASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CROSSVIEW ARM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CONVEX MIRROR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The fender mounted rear view mirror is supplied with or without the heated mirror option. Check the
                type installation and proceed with removal or installation.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900528" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900528.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Fender Mounted Rear-View Mirror (Driver Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SCREW, 10-32 x 1 1/4" SST CRPNH, AND NUT, HEX 10-32 NYLOK SST</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GROMMET, RUBBER 3/16 ID x 7/16 OD x 1/8 GROVE (FOR HEATED MIRRORS WIRE HOLE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MIRROR MOUNTING BASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FORWARD HOOD ATTACHMENT BRACE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MIRROR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. ANGLE BRACE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
